                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Newberry</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-08-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Foster instructs Mr. Newberry to urgently make the following demands in the
                    ease of Dr. Bartlett, at Bourdour: First, for effective protection; second,
                    sufficient pecuniary indemnity; third, punishment of all the guilty; fourth,
                    reprimand of officials if proved remiss; and informs him that a vessel will be
                    sent to investigate if these demands fail.</p>
            </div>
